data.value: In probability theory and statistics, the binomial distribution is N independent is/non-discrete probability distribution of the number of successful trials, wherein the probability of success of each trial is P.Such a single success / failure test is also known as the Bernoulli test.In fact, when n = 1, the binomial distribution is the Bernoulli distribution.Binomial distribution is the basis for binomial experiments with significant differences.
